               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-84-person767">
                  JAMES 
                  HARVEY
               <interp inst="t18310407-84-person767" type="surname" value="HARVEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-84-person767" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-84-person767" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 27th of February I was in the tap-room of the White Lion public-house, in St. Alban's-place, between two and three o'clock - I heard a noise in the bar; I got up, looked through the bar window, and saw the prisoner with this till in his hand - I went into the bar, collared him, and took the till away from him; I sent for the officer - I counted the money in his presence; there were halfpence, pence, and farthings in it, to the amount of 4s. 10d., and these spectacles - Mrs. Sarah Lea is the landlady of the house, and the property is hers; she was out - I was taking care of the house for her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-84-person768">
